    • Method Detail

      • getNewProperty

        public MMProperty getNewProperty(java.lang.String deviceLabel,
                        java.lang.String propertyLabel)
        Returns an instantiated MMProperty from a device and a device property labels. The method retrieves the type of property (Float, Integer or String), the limits and allowed values if applicable. If the device property does not exist, it returns a null object.
        Parameters:
        deviceLabel - Label of the device.
        propertyLabel - Label of the property.
        Returns:
        MMProperty corresponding to the device property, null if the device property does not exist.
